paragraph.content:
any act of voluntary participation in the operation of a ship or of an
                        aircraft with knowledge of facts making it a pirate ship or
                        aircraft;

any act of voluntary participation in the operation of a ship with
                        knowledge of facts making it a ship for armed robbery against
                        ships;

part.text:
(a) to manage and maintain the expeditious flow of information relating to
                incidents of piracy and armed robbery against ships among the Contracting
                Parties;

(c) to prepare statistics and reports on the basis of the information
                gathered and analyzed under subparagraph (b), and to disseminate them to the
                Contracting Parties;

(d) to provide an appropriate alert, whenever possible, to the Contracting
                Parties if there is a reasonable ground to believe that a threat of incidents of
                piracy or armed robbery against ships is imminent;

(e) to circulate requests referred to in Article 10 and relevant information
                on the measures taken referred to in Article 11 among the Contracting
                Parties;
